Emacs comes with an AdvancedDeskCalculator called `calc'.
Try it! `M-x calc'.

AndrewHyatt wrote a number of tutorials on Google+, which have since moved to Github:

* [https://github.com/ahyatt/emacs-calc-tutorials/blob/master/bit_manipulation.org Bit Manipulation]
* [https://github.com/ahyatt/emacs-calc-tutorials/blob/master/calculus.org Calculus]
* [https://github.com/ahyatt/emacs-calc-tutorials/blob/master/financial.org Finances]
* [https://github.com/ahyatt/emacs-calc-tutorials/blob/master/algebra.org Display] -- show square roots and superscripts using ASCII art
* [https://github.com/ahyatt/emacs-calc-tutorials/blob/master/more_algebra.org Algebra]
* [https://github.com/ahyatt/emacs-calc-tutorials/blob/master/fractional_arithmetic.org Fractions]
* [https://github.com/ahyatt/emacs-calc-tutorials/blob/master/strings.org Strings and Binary]
* [https://github.com/ahyatt/emacs-calc-tutorials/blob/master/pi_and_precision.org Pi and Precision]
* [https://github.com/ahyatt/emacs-calc-tutorials/blob/master/unit_conversion.org Units]
* [https://github.com/ahyatt/emacs-calc-tutorials/blob/master/random.org Random Numbers]
* [https://github.com/ahyatt/emacs-calc-tutorials/blob/master/time.org Time] 
* [https://github.com/ahyatt/emacs-calc-tutorials/blob/master/date.org Date] -- also digit grouping
* [https://github.com/ahyatt/emacs-calc-tutorials/blob/master/hex.org Hex Numbers]
